OL,3,CWhy were there so many wildfires this
OL,4,Cyear?
OL,6,FWet weather in 2024 meant there were
OL,7,Ffewer fires but a growth in
OL,8,Fvegetation, providing fuel for future
OL,9,Fwildfires.
OL,11,FThis was followed by the hottest
OL,12,Fspring and summer on record and the
OL,13,Fdriest spring in 100 years in 2025,
OL,14,Faccording to Met Office data.
OL,16,FThe little rain, dry soil and hot
OL,17,Fweather created the perfect conditions
OL,18,Ffor wildfires to spread quickly.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/7
